olive oil
½ carrot
1 bag baby broccoli
1 bag green beans
½ lemon
1 packet mayonnaise
15 g butter
¾ cup water
1 packet couscous
1 packet Currants
1 packet Premium Fillet Steak
1 packet roasted almonds
2 clove garlic
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Preheat BBQ to medium-high heat.
• Grate the carrot (see ingredients). Finely chop
garlic. Halve baby broccoli lengthways. Trim
green beans. Zest lemon to get a good pinch
and slice in half.
• In a small bowl, combine lemon zest,
mayonnaise and a splash of water. Season to
taste and set aside.

• In a medium saucepan heat the butter and a
drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook
garlic and carrot until softened, 2-3 minutes.
• Add the water and a good pinch of salt and
bring to the boil. Add couscous and currants
and stir to combine.
• Cover with a lid and remove from the heat. Set
aside until all the water is absorbed, 5 minutes.
Fluff up with a fork.

• Meanwhile,
place your hand flat on top of premium fillet
steak and slice through horizontally to make two
thin steaks.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef,
Aussie spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil.
• When BBQ is hot, grill beef, 3-5 minutes on each
side for medium-rare or until cooked to your
liking. Transfer to a plate, cover and rest for
5 minutes.

No BBQ? Prep and season beef as above. In a large
frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook beef until cooked through,
3-5 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate and set
aside to rest.

• While the beef is resting, grill lemon, cut side
down, until charred, 4-6 minutes.
• Meanwhile, grill baby broccoli and green
beans until charred and tender, 3-5 minutes on
each side.
• Transfer to a serving plate. Season veggies with
salt and pepper, a drizzle of olive oil and a
good squeeze of grilled lemon juice. Cover to
keep warm.

No BBQ? In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive
oil over high heat. Cook lemon, cut side down, until
charred, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a plate. Return the
frying pan to medium-high and cook baby broccoli
and green beans until lightly golden, 3-5 minutes on
each side.

• Add roasted almonds and a drizzle of olive oil
to the couscous. Stir to combine and season
to taste.

• Slice chargrilled beef fillet. Bring everything to
the table to serve. Help yourself to beef, currant
couscous and BBQ lemony greens.
• Serve with zesty mayo and remaining grilled
lemon. Enjoy!